        "parts": [
          {
            "id": 1150789,
            "content": "Table 1 compares the characteristics of two types of polyethylene used in industrial manufacturing.\n\n| Property | Variation A (HDPE) | Variation B (LDPE) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Molecular Structure | Linear chains | Highly branched chains |\n| Density | $$0.941\u20130.965\\text{ g/cm}^3$$ | $$0.910\u20130.925\\text{ g/cm}^3$$ |\n\nWith reference to their molecular structure, explain why Variation A has a higher density than Variation B.",
            "order": -1,
            "markscheme": "- linear chains have minimal side branching, which allows the polymer molecules to pack more closely together; <marks>1 mark</marks>\n- this tighter packing results in more mass per unit of volume (and higher crystallinity); <marks>1 mark</marks>\n\n_Award <marks>1 mark</marks> for identifying the closer packing of linear chains and <marks>1 mark</marks> for linking this packing density to the overall material density up to <marks>2 marks max</marks>._",
            "marks": 2,
            "label_id": null,
            "rubric_id": null,
            "explanation": null
          },
          {
            "id": 1150790,
            "content": "Describe how the addition of plasticizers modifies the physical properties of Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC) to make it suitable for flexible applications such as medical tubing.",
            "order": 0,
            "markscheme": "- plasticizers are small molecules that sit between the polymer chains, increasing the spacing between them; <marks>1 mark</marks>\n- this reduces the intermolecular forces/prevents the chains from locking, allowing them to slide past one another more easily to increase flexibility/pliability; <marks>1 mark</marks>\n\n_Award <marks>1 mark</marks> for explaining the physical mechanism (increased spacing/interference) and <marks>1 mark</marks> for describing the resulting change in property (reduced forces/increased flexibility) up to <marks>2 marks max</marks>._",
            "marks": 2,
            "label_id": null,
            "rubric_id": null,
            "explanation": null
          }
