            "markscheme": "- Thermosetting plastics contain strong covalent bonds known as cross-links between the polymer chains <marks>1 mark</marks>\n- These cross-links create a rigid 3D network/grid that prevents the chains from sliding over one another when heated <marks>1 mark</marks>\n- As these bonds are permanent and do not break with heat, the material will char or decompose rather than melt/soften <marks>1 mark</marks>\n\n<note>Maximum 3 marks total</note>",
